name: dsm5_1
label: I often used alcohol in large amounts over longer periods of time than I intended.

name: dsm5_2
label: I often wanted or tried to cut down or control my alcohol use.

name: dsm5_3
label: I spent a lot of time either (a) using alcohol, (b) in activities trying to obtain alcohol, or (c) recovering from the effects of my drinking alcohol.

name: dsm5_4
label: I gave up or reduced my involvement in important social, occupational, or recreational activities because of my alcohol use.

name: dsm5_5
label: I continued to use alcohol despite knowing that it likely caused or made worse psychological or physical problems I had (for example, continued drinking alcohol despite knowing it was making my ulcer or depression worse).

name: dsm5_6
label: I found I needed greater amounts of alcohol than I used to in order to feel intoxicated or to get a desired effect, OR I got much less of an effect by using the same amount of alcohol as in the past.

name: dsm5_7
label: I experienced withdrawal symptoms when I tried to cut down or stop drinking alcohol, OR I drank alcohol to relieve or avoid withdrawal symptoms.

name: dsm5_8
label: My alcohol use resulted in my not fulfilling major obligations at work, school, or home (for example, repeated absences or poor performances at work or school; neglecting my children at home).

name: dsm5_9
label: I repeatedly used alcohol in situations that were physically hazardous (for example, driving a car or operating machinery).

name: dsm5_10
label: I have experienced strong desires, urges, or cravings to use alcohol.

name: dsm5_11
label: I continued to use alcohol despite having persistent or recurrent social or interpersonal problems caused or made worse by the effects of my drinking (for example, arguments with friends about my drinking or physical fights).
